page.title: 14FEERINGBURY
page.content: The first landowner was{Harold }the first.After the {Battle of Hastings {William the Conqueror}won it from{ {Harold. William}gave it to the{Bishop {of Westminster.}The garden is six acres. In the two ponds that are in the garden there are some rainbow trout.There is an overshot water wheel which was originally used to pump water up to the house.The River Blackwater flows along the bottom of the garden.The middle part is older than the ends. {Queen Elizabeth}visted the house, she left a piece of glass at the house with her initials on it.
